text:
Five deputies for Gregory Christmas were elected
05 Nov 2019, 13:02 by Infostart
The first meeting of the General Assembly is still in progress. The alternates were individually elected by secret ballot. The youngest member of the pentathlon is 34 and the oldest is 57 years old.
Prior to the election of the Deputy Mayors, the Budapest General Assembly amended the organizational and operational rules of the Municipality of Budapest on the proposal of Mayor Gergely Christmas. Members voted in favor of the amendment by 18 votes to 11 with 1 abstention.
By adopting the proposal, in contrast to the past, the Mayor may submit a draft municipal regulation to the General Assembly with an urgent motion, and members of the capital may now form a political group consisting of at least two members.
With the amendment, MPs also decided to set up a committee on climate protection and the environment and to terminate the post of mayor.
Subsequently, the five deputy mayors were individually elected by secret ballot.

Erzsébet Gy. Németh (DK), 57 years old: First Deputy Head of Human Resources.
Gábor Kerpel-Fronius (Momentum), 54, is in charge of the fight against corruption, including smart city and participation.
Kiss Ambrus, 40, is a general deputy in public administration and finance.
Kata Tüttő (MSZP), 39, became deputy city manager.
David Doros, 34, a Dialogue politician, is responsible for climate protection.



You can find our constantly updated article here!


Past events
Mayor Gergely Christmas has set ten defining values for the next five years of Budapest at the inaugural session of the General Assembly. In a keynote speech at the inaugural meeting, after the swearing-in, Gergely Kar Christmas said that he considered ten fundamental values that he would stick with tooth and nail.

The ten values it lists are:


Budapest has no first- and second-class citizens;
the leaders of the city must serve the interests of the inhabitants;
housing is considered a fundamental right;
they will play their part in the fight against climate change;
protect the built and natural heritage of the city;
give priority to sustainable modes of transport;
ensuring the smooth development of inner and outer districts;
promote cultural diversity;
their capitals should be consulted on all important issues;
Budapest must operate openly, transparently and free from corruption.

Gergely Kar Christmas stated that a new kind of cooperation will be developed with the districts and between Budapest and the government. The capital cannot be subordinate to the current government, only an equal partner - stressed the mayor.
Gergely Christmas said that Budapest is not on one side or the other, the capital of the nation is on us all.

Opening Image: Zoltán Balogh



